Bennu Yıldırımlar
Bennu Yıldırımlar (born 22 November 1969) is a Turkish actress.
Biography.
Bennu Yıldırımlar studied at Erenköy Kız Lisesi and graduated from İstanbul University State Conservatory in 1990. From 1990 to1991, she gained experience at the Westminster Adult Education Institute in London. Yıldırımlar was chosen 'Most Promising new Actress' at the 6th Ankara Film Festival for her role in "Ağrıya Dönüş" in 1994. In 1999, she was given the 'Best Actress' Sadri Alışık award for her performance in the film "Kaç Para Kaç".
She is married to actor Bülent Emin Yarar since 1995.
